{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce the LISA withdrawal penalty.",
        "additional_details": "It is well established that we are living through a cost of living crisis. Last month, the Consumer Price Index hit 9%, the Consumer Prices Index with Housing hit 7.8%, while the Retail Price Index hit 11.1%. Statutory Instrument 2020 No. 506 was designed to support families and savers who faced furlough and a downturn in the economy in the wake of COVID. I would argue that this challenge to families on an economic scale is even more severe now. The LISA withdrawal penalty should, therefore, be reduced.",
        "background": "As with when Statutory Instrument 2020 No. 506 gave effect to the temporary reduction in the withdrawal charge between 6 March 2020 and 5 April 2021 (as laid out on 14 May 2020), the Government should reduce the LISA withdrawal charge from 25% to 20%.",
